<subSubSection id="C36E5BFCE40EFFDFFCC0F8098321FEE0" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="104" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E40EFFDFFCC0F8098321FEE0" blockId="12.[811,1455,1950,2027]" lastBlockId="15.[130,778,215,1498]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="104" pageId="12" pageNumber="101">
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E40EFFDCFCC0F80984D2F80E" authority="Yooprasert, Culham &amp; Utteridge" authorityName="Yooprasert, Culham &amp; Utteridge" authorityYear="2022" box="[813,1451,1950,1975]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brochidodromum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B900D465E40EFFDCFCC0F8098536F80E" box="[813,1103,1950,1974]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="101">Urophyllum brochidodromum</emphasis>
Yooprasert, Culham &amp; Utteridge
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A233691EE40EFFDCFCC3F82E820EF868" box="[814,887,1977,2000]" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E40EFFDCFC0AF82D850EF869" authority="Pit." authorityName="Pit." box="[999,1143,1977,2001]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lecomtei">
<emphasis id="B900D465E40EFFDCFC0AF82D8537F869" box="[999,1102,1977,2001]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="101">toU. lecomtei</emphasis>
Pit.
</taxonomicName>
but differs in the secondary veins strongly joining together to form closed loops close to the leaf margin with no additional sets of loops (conspicuously brochidodromous), while in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E40DFFDFFF3BFF658046FEB1" box="[214,319,241,265]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="15" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lecomtei">
<emphasis id="B900D465E40DFFDFFF3BFF658046FEB1" box="[214,319,241,265]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="104">U. lecomtei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the veins are joined with a series of small loops (festooned brochidodromous). The species also differs in its calyx lobes, which are recurved, at least at the fruiting stage compared to the erect to incurved lobes found in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E40DFFDFFE0AFED6832BFEE1" box="[487,594,321,345]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="15" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lecomtei">
<emphasis id="B900D465E40DFFDFFE0AFED6832BFEE1" box="[487,594,321,345]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="104">U. lecomtei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
